%N A396530 First column of the triangular array with T(0, m) = binomial(2*m, m) and T(n, m) = T(n - 1, m + 3) - 2*T(n - 1, m + 2) + T(n - 1, m + 1).
%C A396530 The rows are generated by iterating the operator E*Delta^2, where E is the forward shift operator, E(f(m)) = f(m + 1), and Delta = E - 1 is the forward difference operator. Thus, E*Delta^2 = E*(E - 1)^2 = E^3 - 2*E^2 + E.
%C A396530 This is the central binomial coefficient analog of A395764, which applies the same operator to the factorial sequence.
%F A396530 a(n) = Sum_{j = 0..2*n} (-1)^j*binomial(2*n, j)*binomial(2*(n + j), n + j).
%F A396530 a(n) = (1/Pi)*Integral_{t = 0..4} t^n*(1 - t)^(2*n)/sqrt(t*(4 - t)) dt.
%e A396530 Triangular array begins:
